Political analyst, Lumkile Mondi, speaks to the #MorningNewsToday team giving an update of elections results from the KZN For full national and provincial results, click here. JOHANNESBURG -  Political analyst Lumkile Mondi says the ANC should consider bringing the DA into a grand coalition to form a national government of unity. Mondi suggested a grand coalition would harken back to the promise of 1996. READ: IEC urgently investigating electoral irregularities "We need to make people believe that we can do it as South Africa and that requires leadership," he said. The political analyst stated president Cyril Ramaphosa would have to go beyond his party's political concerns. READ: Vote counting slower compared to previous election: IEC Mondi said he would be expecting the president to rise and do what is best for the country, not necessarily for the ANC.